<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='719000' id='t-719000'>Either no time delay,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='721000' id='t-721000'>in which case light would just tickle your palm,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='723000' id='t-723000'>or with a time delay of two-tenths of three-tenths of a second.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='727000' id='t-727000'>So the important point here</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='729000' id='t-729000'>is the right hand always does the same things -- sinusoidal movement.</span>
